This paper is likely to belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) category as it deals with the problem of recommendation systems. It could also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) categories as it proposes algorithms for improving the performance of recommender systems. The paper also discusses the idea of incorporating system-level objectives, which could fall under the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) category. Finally, the paper discusses the importance of personalization in recommender systems, which could be relevant to the Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) category.
